  Signing up for PayPal Business

  1. Go to paypal.com and click Sign Up
  2. Choose Business account (not personal)
  3. Enter your email and create a password
  4. Provide business details — name, address, phone, business type
  5. Link a bank account or debit card

  Keys you need for this site:
  - Go to developer.paypal.com → log in with your PayPal account
  - Click Apps & Credentials
  - Create a new app — it generates a Client ID and Secret
  - The Client ID (public) → goes in payment.html in the PayPal <script> tag and in Cloudflare env vars as PAYPAL_CLIENT_ID
  - The Secret (private) → goes in Cloudflare env vars as PAYPAL_CLIENT_SECRET

  PayPal also has a Sandbox environment with test accounts, so you can verify the full flow before real money moves.

  ---
  Recommended order

  1. Sign up for both using test/sandbox credentials first
  2. Drop the test keys into the site and verify the full flow end-to-end
  3. Swap in the live keys only when you're satisfied everything works

  Neither service charges a monthly fee — both take a small percentage per transaction (typically around 2.9% + $0.30 per charge).

